steps.description:
Choose your material wisely, depending on the aesthetic and functional qualities you desire for your trellis. Although a metal trellis can look very ornate and attractive, metal isn’t always the best choice because it can heat up in the sun and burn the plant. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5f/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5f/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Wood is easier to work with and paint, and is more sympathetic to the plant's needs. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/da/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/da/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

When selecting wood, make sure you use kiln-dried wood to avoid warping. Cedar is a popular choice. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/33/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/33/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Consider treating the wood with wood preservative before you work with it: this will prolong the life of your trellis. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/47/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/47/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Get 4 pieces of 2x2 wood, all about 8 feet (2.4 m) in length, plus another 4 pieces of 1x3 wood about 5 feet (1.5 m) in length. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/41/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/41/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Get some shorter lengths for making horizontal cross pieces like the slats on a ladder. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/78/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/78/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet6.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Remember that the wood may be roughly finished, so beware of splinters and use work gloves when handling it. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/01/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet7.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet7.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/01/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet7.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-1Bullet7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

You can make a garden pyramid trellis using pre-cut wood or by cutting your own wood, depending on your skills, experience, and available tools. Cut your wood to size if you need to, otherwise, move to the next step. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/60/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/60/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

You can download free cutting guides for woodworking that may make the job easier by telling you how and where to cut. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3a/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3a/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

A mitre saw will probably be essential if you are cutting your own wood to size. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/24/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/24/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you plan to keep the structure in place for a while, consider preparing the area before placing it. Dig some manure or compost into the ground. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/27/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/27/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Remove stones and weed the area before placing your pyramid trellis. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Be aware that if you dig first, the ground may settle and the pyramid may sink a little over time. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/64/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/64/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If the feet sit in damp ground, they are more likely to rot or crack. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/40/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/40/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Soaking the lower part of the structure (or all of it) in wood preservative overnight will help prolong the life of your trellis. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/77/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/77/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If possible, place it on hard, free-draining ground because the trellis won’t last as long if it sits in wet earth or a puddle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/86/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/86/Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet6.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Pyramid-Trellis-Step-8Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
